main event: A observer sighted and photographed three dull white objects in the sky on June 19, 1967 in Colorado.
interesting points: The objects were described as dull white in color and were photographed by the observer.
The observer was on the ground at the time of the sighting.
Project Blue Book concluded the sighting was a probable reflection.
The photographs were analyzed and determined to be photographic phenomena reflecting objects outside the camera, rather than unidentified flying objects.
